# INFTOUR — full localization for new text

## Languages (required for every string)

Use **all eight** locales from `Lang` in `app/lib/langStore.ts`:

`eng`, `esp`, `ru`, `fr`, `it`, `de`, `uk`, `pl`

- **`uk`** is **Ukrainian** in this project (not British English).
- **`esp`** is Spanish; **`eng`** is English.

Every new or changed user-visible string must have a value for **each** of these keys. Do not ship with only English/Spanish.

## Source of truth (priority)

1. **If the user attaches or points to an official copy file** (e.g. `.docx`, `.md`, a dedicated `*_translations.ts`, or pasted blocks per language), **use that text** for each locale. Match wording, punctuation, and terminology from the file; only adapt formatting (e.g. `\n`, `**bold**`) if the UI expects it.
2. **If no file or per-language text is provided**, **translate yourself** into all eight languages: natural, tourist-friendly tone consistent with existing INFTOUR copy; keep proper names (Calpe, Costa Blanca, INFTOUR, product names) as in the rest of the site.

## Where to put strings

- **Feature-specific maps**: add or extend the relevant `*_translations.ts` (or section file) next to the feature, using the same shape as existing entries:

  `Record<string, { eng; esp; ru; fr; it; de; uk; pl }>`.

- **Merge into `useLangStore`**: spread the map into the big `translations` object in `app/lib/langStore.ts` if it is not already imported.
- **Top bar / “translation” locale strip** (weather, webcams, “Now in Calpe”, close labels, etc.): whenever that UI’s visible text changes, update `app/components/TopBar/topbar_translations.ts` for **all eight** languages. If you add strings shown next to the site language switcher or main nav, also cover those via `menu_translations.ts` or the relevant map.

## Implementation checklist

- Replace hardcoded JSX text with `t("yourKey")` (or the project’s pattern) and define `yourKey` in the correct map.
- Reuse an existing key if the meaning is identical; otherwise add a new key in **all** languages.
- After edits, ensure **no** language column is missing, empty, or left as a copy-paste duplicate of English unless intentional.

## Consistency

- Align terminology with nearby strings in the same feature (e.g. modal + card + menu).
- Long copy (modals, FAQ): keep structure parallel across languages (same paragraphs/bullets).
